                            <comment id="115423" author="grussell" created="Fri, 8 May 2015 08:59:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Regarding your comment on the question (in response to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=abilan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;abilan&quot;&gt;Artem Bilan&lt;/a&gt; work-around)...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve tried this solution as well. It works for this simple case (Thread.sleep()), but does not work when listener is doing &quot;real&quot; job with long-waiting IO for example.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s nothing the framework can do if user code is in an uninterruptible state such as waiting on a socket I/O. You need to close the socket somehow.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or call &lt;tt&gt;System.exit&lt;/tt&gt; after closing the context.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="116951" author="grussell" created="Tue, 23 Jun 2015 06:39:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged (on May 11 !)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
